{
  "stem": "22237.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I got back to Frankfurt, I-- the first thing I did is I had forgotten to mention that I had-- before I was deported, I worked in a store to-- I learned to make hats, to become a milliner, to make hats.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was there about a year maybe, not quite a year, and I liked it very much.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I figured, this way, I will be able to do dressmaking, and I'll be able to make hats when I-- when I emigrate.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the only thing we had on our mind.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was nothing else on our mind, you know-- to get out of Germany, and make a life for yourself, and to work.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when I returned, the boss that I worked for-- and her name was Mrs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Friedman.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She had a millinery store, a hat store, on the main street of Frankfurt, called it Zeil.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Z-E-I-L.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I visit-- I went to the store, and I-- and she, she embraced me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She didn't know what to do with me because she couldn't understand why I didn't come to work until she learned that the Polish Jews were deported.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then she figured out that I must have been there also.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So she was the first person I, I'd been to see.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She gave me shelter, she let me stay in her house for a few days.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I didn't go to work because I-- at that time, I was too exhausted, and too-- and also I didn't-- I was afraid because I was supposed to be-- I was supposed to be over in Poland, or someplace.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I wasn't supposed to be home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't know whether-- I didn't know at the time that other Polish Jews were coming back, were sent back.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
